<plot>Nine strangers gather at a rural farmhouse in Maryland to undergo heart-wrenching treatment for their worst childhood traumas or abuse. At the core of this six-part documentary series - featuring controversial psychodrama therapy and filmed as it happened over the 5-day intensive workshop - is the "family Structure," in which participants relive their traumas in order to heal from them.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?082431</url></doc>
